		<entry>
		<author><name><![CDATA[tzuk]]></name></author>
		<updated>2013-07-18T07:38:22-04:00</updated>

		<published>2013-07-18T07:38:22-04:00</published>
		<id>https://forums.sandboxie.com/phpBB3/viewtopic.php?t=15965&amp;p=92004#p92004</id>
		<link href="https://forums.sandboxie.com/phpBB3/viewtopic.php?t=15965&amp;p=92004#p92004"/>
		<title type="html"><![CDATA[Sandboxie 4.02/4.04 not fully compatible with EMET 4.0]]></title>

		
		<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.sandboxie.com/phpBB3/viewtopic.php?t=15965&amp;p=92004#p92004"><![CDATA[
I looked into this and I can see the problem, but I don't know if I am going to fix it.<br><br>The thing is that I want to prevent the "application compatibility layer" DLL (AppHelp.dll) from loading into Sandboxie programs like Start.exe because if one mistakenly sets the option "run this program in compatibility mode for another versions of Windows" then it introduces strange problems in  Sandboxie.  This has happened in the past.<br><br>On the other hand, EMET is relying on that DLL to inject itself into programs, and therein lies the problem, because Start.exe does not load the AppHelp.dll.<br><br>Now one kind of fix is to run your browser as a forced program and then Start.exe is not involved and EMET DLLs are injected correctly, but I understand not everyone uses the forced program feature.<br><br>So a possible workaround is to create a special shortcut that uses an intermediate program.  Right-click New &gt; Shortcut on the desktop, then paste:<br><div class="codebox"><p>CODE: </p><pre><code>"C:\Program Files\Sandboxie\Start.exe" explorer "C:\Program Files\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe"</code></pre></div>So you're getting Explorer.exe to launch Internet Explorer (or whatever browser) and Explorer.exe will load AppHelp.dll and will inject EMET into the new process it is starting.<br><br>Hope this helps.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.sandboxie.com/phpBB3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">tzuk</a> — Thu Jul 18, 2013 7:38 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
